<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-28T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-28T07:00:00-05:00" n="163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/776.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                        Germany</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-28T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The German Government has reached our own conclusion that common
                                action even in the matter of finance is the wisest policy for the
                                concerned powers to pursue for the protection of the common
                                interests in China, and consequently has expressed its willingness
                                to have Russia and Japan admitted into the financial group.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Leishman.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>